  <h1>buoy onboard</h1>

  <p>
    Set up AI guardrails so tools like Claude, Copilot, and Cursor understand and follow
    your design system. Creates skill files and updates CLAUDE.md in one command.
  </p>

  <h2>Usage</h2>

  <pre><code>buoy onboard [options]</code></pre>

  <h2>What It Does</h2>

  <ol>
    <li><strong>Scans</strong> your codebase for components and tokens</li>
    <li><strong>Identifies</strong> patterns and anti-patterns</li>
    <li><strong>Creates</strong> skill files at <code>.claude/skills/design-system/</code></li>
    <li><strong>Updates</strong> CLAUDE.md with design system context</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Options</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Option</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--skill-only</code></td>
        <td>Only create skill files, skip CLAUDE.md</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--context-only</code></td>
        <td>Only update CLAUDE.md, skip skill files</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--dry-run</code></td>
        <td>Show what would be created without writing files</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>--json</code></td>
        <td>Output result as JSON</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

